CHANGELOG.md:7:- Added depth-2 sw_sampler end-to-end test coverage (frac-0116): `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` now includes `SwSamplerEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef source and the SC-side runtime harness `my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd` through one diagnostic lifecycle. The test extracts every documented SynthDef control default (`bufnum`, `amp`, `grain_size_ms=80.0`, `density=12.0`, `position`, `position_rate`, `pitch_transpose_semitones`, `pitch_jitter_semitones`, `attack_sec`, `release_sec`, `gate>=1`, `out_bus=0`, `fx_bus`, `fx_send=0.4`), verifies the integrated granular signal-chain order (`Impulse.kr` -> `TRand.kr` -> `.midiratio` -> `Sweep.ar`/`Phasor.ar` -> `GrainBuf.ar(... bufnum ...)` -> `EnvGen.kr(Env.asr, gate, doneAction: 2)` -> dry `Out.ar(out_bus, ...)` -> parallel `Out.ar(fx_bus, ...)` send) on a comment-stripped source, confirms the dry write to `out_bus` is not scaled by `fx_send` so the parallel-send architecture is preserved, inspects the SC-side runtime harness for source compile, 2-second render, non-silence, FFT spectral peak, gate=0 release tail, and known-content buffer allocation, and round-trips a JSON-safe diagnostic of the SynthDef name, source path, runtime-harness path, defaults, signal-chain stages, stage positions, and runtime checks through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_sw_sampler_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the SCD source and SC-side harness already produced the required one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4669 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:9:- Added depth-2 startle end-to-end test coverage (frac-0115): `tests/test_startle.py` now includes `StartleEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `senseweave.startle` public surface through one deterministic lifecycle with a monkeypatched clock. The test proves quiet input stays calm, a loud RMS spike creates a startled state and surprised face reaction, a second spike during cooldown is blocked, later spikes after cooldown but inside the 30-second recent-startle window increment the count to three, `should_mute_output(...)` recommends muting, and a primitive quiet/first-startle/cooldown/third-startle diagnostic round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_startle_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `senseweave.startle` already produced the required one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:11:- Added depth-2 sampler-scheduler end-to-end test coverage (frac-0114): `tests/test_sampler_scheduler.py` now includes `SamplerSchedulerEndToEndTests`, which drives `senseweave.sampler_scheduler` through one realistic scheduling lifecycle: `density_for_mode("evening_reflection")` resolves through `DEFAULT_SAMPLER_DENSITY_BY_MODE` to `0.65`, `count_sampler_events(0.65, 16, Random(42))` returns the documented `floor(0.65 * 16) + Bernoulli(0.65)` count under a deterministic RNG, `plan_sampler_phrase_indices(0.65, 16, Random(42))` returns sorted, unique, in-range phrase indices whose length matches that count, and a primitive diagnostic of the mode/density/count/indices round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_sampler_scheduler_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `senseweave.sampler_scheduler` already produced the required one-path floor + Bernoulli + sorted-sample output; startup identity anchors remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
