CHANGELOG.md:203:- Added depth-2 rollout control report helpers (frac-0021): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/rollout_controls.py` now exposes frozen `RolloutFlagState` and `RolloutControlReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `flag_state`, `rollout_control_report`, and `summarize_rollout_controls` so operator/status callers can inspect the resolved SenseWeave rollout flags, raw environment values, default/defaulted/env source, enabled/disabled counts, and effective self-critique state without changing existing flag defaults. Existing `SenseWeaveFeatureFlags`, `load_feature_flags`, and downstream practice-curriculum, self-critique, and piece-commission behavior are preserved; `tests/test_rollout_controls.py` pins the new report surface, downstream end-to-end use, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_senseweave_rollout_controls.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:205:- Added depth-2 silence budget report helpers (frac-0020): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/silence_budget.py` now exposes frozen `LaneSilenceBudgetStat` and `SilenceBudgetReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_silence_budget_stat`, `analyze_silence_budget`, and `summarize_silence_budget_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R10 rule once and inspect per-lane phrase outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, original phrase count, breath-extension count, tacet step count, distinct tacet phrase count, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TARGET_DENSITY`, `DEFAULT_THRESHOLD`, `SilenceBudgetRule.apply`, and `apply_silence_budget` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_silence_budget_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_silence_budget_depth.py` pins tacet-trigger lane shaping, breath-extension lane shaping, non-melodic non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:207:- Added depth-2 punctuation report helpers (frac-0019): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/punctuation.py` now exposes frozen `LanePunctuationStat` and `PunctuationReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_punctuation_stat`, `analyze_punctuation`, and `summarize_punctuation_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R6 punctuation rule once and inspect per-lane phrase-terminal outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, terminal-note count, extended-terminal count, inserted-breath count, mean terminal multiplier, mean breath milliseconds, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `MAX_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `PunctuationRule.apply`, and `apply_punctuation` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_punctuation_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_punctuation_depth.py` pins melody shaping, non-melodic and lane-grid-locked non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:209:- Added depth-2 duration contrast report helpers (frac-0018): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/duration_contrast.py` now exposes frozen `LaneDurationContrastStat` and `DurationContrastReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_duration_contrast_stat`, `analyze_duration_contrast`, and `summarize_duration_contrast_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R4 rule once and read back per-lane shaping outcomes (lane name, role, step count, shaped-step count, mean rendered/original length ratio, longest-row and shortest-row indices, and an `applies` flag for role-gated and grid-locked-metadata lanes), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary (totals, lane counts, applied-lane count, per-lane entries) without re-walking the tracker scene tree. Existing `MIN_MULTIPLIER`, `MAX_MULTIPLIER`, `DurationContrastRule.apply`, and `apply_duration_contrast` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_duration_contrast_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_duration_contrast_depth.py` pins per-step length-ratio counting, non-melodic and grid-locked-lane non-application, scene/song aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:211:- Added depth-2 metric accent report helpers (frac-0017): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/metric_accent.py` now exposes frozen `LaneMetricAccentStat` and `MetricAccentReport` dataclasses plus `lane_metric_accent_stat`, `analyze_metric_accent`, and `summarize_metric_accent_report` so diagnostics can apply the R1 rule once and inspect per-lane shaping outcomes (lane name, role, meter, step count, shaped-step count, mean multiplier, strongest row, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `METRIC_ACCENT_4_4`, `metric_accent_table`, `MetricAccentRule.apply`, and `apply_metric_accent` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_metric_accent_depth.py` pins the new report surface and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_metric_accent_rule.py`, `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py`, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:213:- Added depth-2 lung capacity report helpers (frac-0016): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/lung_capacity.py` now exposes frozen `LaneBreathStat` and `LungCapacityReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_breath_stat`, `analyze_lung_capacity`, and `summarize_lung_capacity_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R11 rule once and read back per-lane breath outcomes (lane name, voice, role, resolved capacity seconds, inserted vs. tagged breath counts, and an `applies` flag for role-gated wind/voice lanes), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary (totals, lane counts, applied-lane count, per-lane entries) without re-walking the tracker scene tree. Existing `LungCapacityRule.apply`, `apply_lung_capacity`, and `lung_capacity_seconds_for_voice` semantics are preserved so MIDI/Theramini/score-tree callers and `tests/test_lung_capacity_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_lung_capacity_depth.py` pins inserted-vs-tagged counting, non-wind lane non-application, scene/song aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:215:- Added depth-2 render ablation helpers (frac-0015): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/ablation.py` now exposes frozen `AblationCase`, `AblationResult`, and `AblationSuite` dataclasses plus `rule_identifiers`, `build_ablation_cases`, `run_ablation_suite`, and `summarize_ablation_suite` so CCH-010 tooling can plan single-rule or custom ablation cases, render a full-stack baseline, execute each case through the existing `ablate()` seam, and return JSON-safe operator summaries with changed/unchanged counts. Existing `ablate()` behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_render_ablation.py` now pins suite planning, custom pair handling, summary output, and fractal depth >= 2, while debugger/listener-review and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:217:- Added depth-2 production course helpers (frac-0014): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/production_course.py` now exposes frozen `CourseSummary`, `ChapterDigest`, `ArcPhaseSnapshot`, and `CourseArcPlan` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_course`, `chapter_digest`, `catalog_digest`, `arc_phase_snapshot`, `arc_phase_snapshots`, `course_titles`, `plan_course_arc`, and `validate_course` so runtime diagnostics and tests can render an operator-readable view of a section course (chapter count, transition type, mix role, resolved concept titles in declared chapter order), digest each chapter with its first three sample concept values, snapshot every required arc phase with a `sparse` / `balanced` / `dense` density bucket, plan an arc end-to-end by reusing `course_for_section` across a sequence of section descriptors with the last transition cleanly resolving to `terminal`, and report unknown-value chapters as a sorted tuple. Existing `REQUIRED_CHAPTER_IDS`, `REQUIRED_PHASE_NAMES`, `COURSE_CHAPTERS`, `ARC_PHASE_PROFILES`, `load_course_chapters`, `load_arc_phase_profiles`, `course_chapter`, `course_concept`, `arc_phase_profile`, `transition_type_for_section`, and `course_for_section` semantics are preserved so the score-tree composer and `tests/test_production_course_knowledge_base.py` / `tests/test_production_course_integration.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_production_course_depth.py` pins summary title order, chapter digest metadata + `KeyError` on unknown ids, catalog digest coverage, density bucketing + `KeyError` on unknown phase, end-to-end arc plan + empty short-circuit, and validator behavior, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:219:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:221:- Added depth-2 genre literacy helpers (frac-0012): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/genre_literacy.py` now exposes frozen `GenreSummary` / `GenreBlend` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_strategy`, `genre_compatibility`, `blend_genre_strategies`, and `recommend_genre_sequence` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can render a stable per-genre summary (label, tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, voice count, dominant grooves, top arc phases, calm/balanced/intense mood bucket), score a bounded `[0.0, 1.0]` symmetric compatibility between two traditions from arc-affinity cosine, modal/groove Jaccard ratios, and texture/chromatic distance, blend numeric hints with a clamped `[0.0, 1.0]` weight (tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, rubato tolerance, repetition tolerance, spatial width, sorted shared modal preferences), and plan one genre per supplied arc phase with rolling fatigue from prior selections. Existing `GenreStrategy`/`REQUIRED_GENRES` data, `strategy_for_genre`, `all_strategies`, `genre_arc_affinity`, `best_genres_for_phase`, and `select_genre` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_genre_literacy_depth.py` pins summary stability and mood bucketing, compatibility self-identity / symmetry / boundedness with related-vs-contrasted ranking, blend interpolation / clamp / modal intersection, sequence per-phase coverage with no immediate repeats, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:223:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:225:- Added depth-2 generation client_protocol helpers (frac-0010): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` now exposes a frozen `GenerationOutcome` dataclass plus pure helpers `cost_per_second`, `result_summary`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` so any backend (Replicate, Modal, local Ada, fakes) can compute USD-per-second cost from a `GenerationResult`, render a stable operator-readable summary dict (rounded duration / cost / per-second cost), emit a single-line `model=… dur=…s cost=$… latency=…ms id=…` log entry with `<unknown>` substituted for an empty `api_request_id`, and validate a result against its `GenerationRequest` (model match, sample-rate floor, duration tolerance, non-negative cost, non-negative latency) into a typed pass/fail outcome with stable reason ordering. The existing `GenerationResult` field order, `GenerationClient` Protocol contract, and downstream `client_replicate` / `client_modal` / `client_local` paths are preserved; `tests/test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins outcome shape, zero-duration cost handling, summary rounding, log-line ID fallback, and accumulated validation reasons, while existing client protocol, Replicate retry, Modal, local-Ada, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:227:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:229:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
CHANGELOG.md:231:- Added depth-2 collaborative canvas helpers (frac-0007): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/collaborative_canvas.py` now exposes `canvas_layer_manifest`, `canvas_summary`, and `render_text_canvas` so the shared installation canvas can produce stable operator-readable layer metadata, meaningful layer/count/bounds summaries, and a deterministic fixed-size text rendering from persisted canvas state. Existing layer mutation and JSON state round-trip behavior is preserved; `tests/test_collaborative_canvas_depth.py` pins manifest ordering, summary counts and bounds, priority-based text composition, JSON round-trip rendering, and fractal depth >= 2.
CHANGELOG.md:233:- Added depth-2 character registry helpers (frac-0006): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/character_registry.py` now exposes pure helpers `voice_of`, `mode_gain_for`, `params_for`, `summarize_registry`, `voices_by_role`, and `find_voices_by_synth` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can project voice metadata, resolve per-mode gain overrides, merge voice params with caller overrides (skipping `None`-valued overrides), and inspect the registry without reaching into raw mapping shapes. Malformed `voice` entries are ignored across the diagnostic helpers, gain overrides coerce through `float()` with default fallback on non-numeric values, and bucketed/match outputs are deterministically sorted. Existing `CharacterRegistry`, `VOICE_SAMPLER_*` constants, `SAMPLER_DEFAULT_PARAMS`, and `SAMPLER_MODE_GAIN_OVERRIDES` are preserved so `cast_planner`, `duet_composer`, and `tests/test_character_registry.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_character_registry_depth.py` pins voice projection, gain override resolution, params merge with `None`-skip, registry summary histograms, role-bucket sorting, synth-match filtering, and fractal depth ≥ 2.
CHANGELOG.md:235:- Added depth-2 archive path layout helpers (frac-0005): `my-claw/tools/archive_paths.py` now exposes `ArchivePathLayout`, `resolve_archive_layout`, `archive_layout_summary`, and `prepare_archive_layout` so archive daemon outputs, rendered sample events, camera capture rings, and Litestream backups can be resolved and prepared as one typed storage layout while preserving the existing resolver functions. Regression coverage in `tests/test_archive_paths.py` pins root-source metadata, summary output, directory creation, legacy resolver compatibility, and fractal depth >= 2.
CHANGELOG.md:237:- Added depth-2 narrative arc helpers (frac-0004): `my-claw/tools/inner_life/narrative_arc.py` now exposes pure helpers `phase_at`, `phase_progress`, `phase_profile`, and `arc_summary` for resolving the 30-minute build/rise/climax/resolve/rest cycle without mutating an `InnerState`, with clamped position lookup, per-phase progress fractions, and stable diagnostic labels (`gathering`, `rising`, `peaking`, `resolving`, `resting`, `unknown`). `complete_cycle` now aggregates `today_events` into an `event_type_counts` histogram (bucketing missing/blank `type` keys under `unknown`), counts opinions, and records `final_phase`/`final_position` alongside the existing cycle/duration/mood/mode keys. Existing `update_arc`, `start_new_cycle`, `energy_for_phase`, and `action_weight_for_phase` semantics are preserved so `decision_engine` and `inner_life.main` callers are unaffected; `tests/test_narrative_arc_depth.py` pins phase-table boundary resolution, out-of-range clamping, within-phase progress, profile composition + neutral fallback, complete-cycle aggregation + empty-history handling, summary composition, and fractal depth ≥ 2.
CHANGELOG.md:239:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:241:- Added depth-2 X11 gallery wrapper helpers (frac-0002): `my-claw/tools/gallery_x11.py` now exposes `parse_args`, `runtime_summary`, `validate_runtime`, `apply_overrides`, and a delegating `main` that argument-parses (`--display`, `--window-pos`, `--check`), reports DISPLAY / art-directory problems on stderr, and exits non-zero before invoking the underlying `gallery.gallery_x11.main()` when the runtime is unhealthy. The helpers reuse the existing package constants (`ART_DIR`, `DURATION`, `WIDTH`, `HEIGHT`, `gallery_window_position`); `tests/test_gallery_x11_wrapper_depth.py` pins parsed-args, summary, validation, override application, and `--check` / failure / clean-delegation behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:245:- Added depth-2 EMSD catalog helpers (frac-0001): `my-claw/curriculum/catalog.py` now exposes grouped category lookup, semester filtering, prerequisite graph output, stable exercise indexing, compact summary statistics, and catalog consistency validation. The helpers are pure, typed, and keep the existing 40-course catalog/scaffold contract unchanged; `tests/test_emsd_catalog_depth.py` pins meaningful helper output and validation error reporting.
CHANGELOG.md:259:- Added face/inkplate generation status support (T-018): Added `generation_status()` to `my-claw/tools/senseweave/operator_diagnostics.py` which reads `/tmp/generation_status.json` and parses `queue_depth` and `is_generating` to return a dictionary suitable for face/inkplate rendering, along with a `caption` field computing the status message (`♫ queued: N`, `♫ generating`, or `♫ ready`). Includes tests verifying parsing logic and missing/corrupt file fallback in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`.
CHANGELOG.md:303:- Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.
CHANGELOG.md:323:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
CHANGELOG.md:325:- Fixed recalled motif rhythm metadata so later sections that borrow earlier material inherit the current scene's rhythm/progression profile instead of leaking the source scene's old `rhythm_development`.
CHANGELOG.md:379:- Tightened title-hook coherence again: `hook_engine.py` now chooses title phrases from image-field-aware pools that also react to cadence, progression profile, hook type, and repertoire source titles, so CypherClaw can move between labels like `Low Light`, `Electric Circuits`, `Moving Lines`, and `Open Thresholds` without collapsing back to generic or repeated adjective-noun pairs.
CHANGELOG.md:388:- Extended repertoire influence into tracker form memory: the live composer can now inherit a prior strong song's preferred progression profile, title/hook recall mode, form variant, and section-density bias before building the next tracker song.
CHANGELOG.md:389:- Made repertoire memory active instead of archival-only: `repertoire_memory.py` now returns forward-looking influence by family/cadence, `hook_engine.py` can answer or recall prior title/hook material, and the live composer can bias the next song's progression profile before score generation begins.
CHANGELOG.md:395:- Diversified family and harmonic planning across the day and week: `resolve_tracker_plan()` now rotates through day-phase and weekly-phase family palettes instead of pinning occupied daytime songs to one family, and it emits progression profiles like `open_day`, `lift`, `settling`, and `experiment` so the score generator changes chord motion as well as form.
CHANGELOG.md:396:- Added family-level motif memory to the live tracker path: `ContinuousLearner` now tags songs with tracker family, progression profile, cadence state, and patch context, `MelodicMemory` can retrieve matching fragments by keyword, and `score_from_mood()` now prefers and answers same-family/profile motifs instead of drawing only from a generic recent fragment pool.
CHANGELOG.md:398:- Gave the named house patches real musical identities instead of just voice pools: `score_from_mood()` is now patch-aware, so melody contour, bass/comping pattern, progression bank, dynamics, and register spread all change with the active house patch.
CHANGELOG.md:435:- Added a queue-backed Telegram `/monitor` built-in so live queue progress and active task status come from the authority DB instead of stale routed status text.
CHANGELOG.md:436:- Unified queue-progress totals across Telegram and `sdp-cli`: counts now use live executable tasks and exclude only split parents.
CHANGELOG.md:440:- Added the missing `OPT-005` half-hour Telegram heartbeat in the live daemon scheduler, including uptime, I/O wait, memory, load, available-agent count, queue progress, pet XP summary, and Observatory logging.
